<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Hardening H-2: deliberately near-empty. AskMail is NOT sandboxed — Full
  Disk Access plus scanning ~/Library/Mail is incompatible with the App
  Sandbox (docs/ollama-onboarding-spec.md) — so this file does not add
  com.apple.security.app-sandbox.

  It exists to pin get-task-allow=false and to document, by omission, that
  the app claims none of the entitlements that would weaken the hardened
  runtime's anti-injection defenses:
    - com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation
    - com.apple.security.cs.disable-executable-page-protection
    - com.apple.security.cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables
    - com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory
    - com.apple.security.get-task-allow (true)
  None of these are needed: AskMail links only system frameworks + the
  system libsqlite3 (see Package.swift), and spawns `ollama` as a separate
  signed process (OllamaEngine.swift) rather than loading anything into
  this process — library validation covers that with zero relaxation.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>com.apple.security.get-task-allow</key>
	<false/>
</dict>
</plist>
